{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀλήθ-εια</b> [ᾰλ], ἡ, <br /> <i>Doric dialect</i> ἀλάθεια (also ἀλαθείᾱ[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus 12.204); ἀλάθεα 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus 57, 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 29.1 is _neuter_ _plural_ of ἀλᾱθή; _Epic dialect_ (and Farly _Attic dialect_ _accusative_ to Hdn.Gr. 2.454)\">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>] ἀληθεί; <i>Ionic dialect</i> ἀληθείη: <br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> <b>truth</b>, opposed to <b>lie</b> or <b>mere appearance</b>: <br /><Level3><b>__I.1</b></Level3> in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] only opposed to <b>a lie</b>, frequently in phrase ἀληθείην καταλέξαι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 24.407, +others; ἀ. ἀποειπεῖν 23.361\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; παιδὸς πᾶσαν ἀ. μυθεῖσθαι to tell whole <b>truth</b> about the lad, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 11.507; ἀλάθει᾽ ἀτρεκής 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 5.17, compare 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus [same place] \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; proverbial, οἶνος καὶ ἀ. `<b>in vino veritas'</b>, Alc.[same place], etc.; ἁπλᾶ γάρ ἐστι τῆς ἀ. ἔπη[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Fragmenta - American Journal of Philology” 176, compare 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Phoenissae” 469; χρᾶσθαι τῇ ἀ. 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.116; εἰπεῖν τὴν ἀ. [prev. author] 6.69; ἡ ἀ. περί τινος 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.122, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 91\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀ. ἔχειν to be <b>true</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1281a42: _plural_, ταῖς ἀ. χρῆσθαι 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 9.5; τὰς ἀ. λέγειν 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 87, 925; τὰς ἀ. ἀκοῦσαι τῶν γενομένων 4th c.BC: Alcidamas Rhetor “Ὀδυσσεύς.” 13:—Ἀλήθεια or περὶ Ἀληθείας, title of works by 5th c.BC: Protagoras Philosophus, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 161c, “Cra.” 391c; by 5th c.BC: Antipho Sophista, “FOxy.” 1364, compare 2nd c.AD: Hermogenes Rhetor “περὶ ἰδεῶν” 2.11, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.2</b></Level3> after [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] also <b>truth, reality</b>, opposed to <b>appearance</b>, σὺν ἀλαθείᾳ καλῶν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus 3.96; ἡ ἀ. τῶν πραχθέντων 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 2.4.1; τῶν ἔργων ἡ ἀ. 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.41; μιμήματα ἀληθείας 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Politicus” 300c:\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] — in <i>adverbial</i> usages, τῇ ἀ. <b>in very truth</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.120, etc.; ταῖς ἀ. 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 15.283, compare 4th-3rd c.BC: Philemo Comicus 130, 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 10.40.5, 2nd c.AD: Babrius Fabularum Scriptor 75.20; rarely (without the _Article_) ἀληθείᾳ 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 343d:—with Preps., ἐν τῇ ἀ. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Laches” 183d\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐπὶ τῆς ἀληθείας καὶ τοῦ πράγματος <b>in truth and reality</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.72\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ἐπ᾽ ἀληθείᾳ <b>for the sake of truth</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 628, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 891\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also, <b>according to truth and nature</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 7.44:— μετ᾽ ἀληθείας 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 2.1.27, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 2.4:— κατὰ τὴν ἀ. 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 1.2.46, etc.; κατ᾽ ἀλήθειον 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1278b33, etc.:— ξὺν ἀληθείᾳ 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1567:— πρὸς ἀλήθειαν 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 5.67, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.3</b></Level3> <b>real war</b>, opposed to <b>exercise</b> or <b>parade</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 10.20.4, +others; ἐπ᾽ αὐτῆς τῆς ἀ. [prev. author] 1.21.3. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.4</b></Level3> <b>true event, realization</b> of dream or omen, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.64, Damon cited in Scholia 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 1003. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> of persons, <b>truthfulness, sincerity</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.55; ἀλαθείᾳ φρενῶν 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1550, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 331c, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Nicomachea” 1108a20. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> *)a. personified, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Empedocles Poeta Philosophus 1, 4th-5th c.BC: Parmenides Poeta Philosophus 1.29, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> <b>symbol of truth, jewel</b> worn by Egyptian high-priest, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 1.48, 75, 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus “Varia Historia” 14.34\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]: of the Thummim, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Lev.8.8.\">LXX</a>]","strongNumber":"G0225","accentedUnicode":"ἀλήθεια","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0226","matchingForm":"ἀληθεύω","stepTransliteration":"alētheuō","gloss":"be truthful","_zh_tw_Gloss":"說真理","_es_Gloss":"ser honesto","_zh_Gloss":"说真理"},{"strongNumber":"G0227","matchingForm":"ἀληθής","stepTransliteration":"alēthēs","gloss":"true","_zh_tw_Gloss":"真實","_es_Gloss":"verdadero","_zh_Gloss":"真实"},{"strongNumber":"G0228","matchingForm":"ἀληθινός","stepTransliteration":"alēthinos","gloss":"true","_zh_tw_G